cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.DC 

This paper deals with the performance of network-assisted D2D communication, which is a subfield of wireless networking and communication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves optimization and resource allocation, which falls under the category of cs.IT (Information Theory). The use of relay nodes and the distributed solution approach suggest the possibility of system-level design and control, which could be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also mentions the use of LTE-Advanced networks, which is a subfield of multimedia communication and could be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper involves message passing techniques, which could be categorized under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
